# Client Chats Module — Architecture Reference

This document describes the full structure and working logic of the Client Chats (Inbox Integrations) module. It covers the backend NestJS services, frontend Next.js components, database schema, WebSocket real-time layer, and the queue/assignment system.

---

## Overview

The Client Chats module is a multi-channel messaging inbox that connects WhatsApp, Telegram, Viber, Facebook Messenger, and a web chat widget into a unified CRM interface. Operators handle conversations, managers oversee queues and analytics, and the system auto-matches customers to CRM clients.

### Tech Stack
- **Backend**: NestJS, Prisma ORM, PostgreSQL, Socket.IO
- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 (App Router), React, Tailwind CSS, Recharts
- **Channels**: WhatsApp (Meta Cloud API), Telegram (Bot API), Viber (Chat API), Facebook (Graph API), Web Chat (custom widget)

