### Core Service (`clientchats-core.service.ts`)

This is the central service. Key methods:

| Method | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `processInbound(channelType, channelAccountId, parsed)` | Main inbound pipeline: dedup → upsert participant → upsert conversation → save message → auto-match → emit events |
| `upsertParticipant(channelType, channelAccountId, parsed)` | Create/update participant with "best name wins" guard |
| `upsertConversation(channelType, channelAccountId, externalConversationId, participantId)` | Create new or update existing conversation; archives CLOSED conversations and creates new chain link |
| `saveMessage(data)` | Persist message to DB with participant/sender relations |
| `sendReply(conversationId, userId, text, media?)` | Send agent reply via channel adapter, save message, emit events |
| `listConversations(query)` | List with filters (channel, status, assigned, search) and pagination |
| `getConversation(id)` | Single conversation with all relations |
| `assignConversation(conversationId, userId)` | Manual assign/unassign by manager |
| `changeStatus(conversationId, status)` | Close/reopen conversation |
| `deleteConversation(conversationId)` | Delete conversation and entire history chain |

### Inbound Message Flow

```
Webhook → Guard (signature verify) → Public Controller → Adapter.parseInbound()
  → CoreService.processInbound()
    → dedup by externalMessageId
    → upsertParticipant (with best-name-wins guard)
    → upsertConversation (stores participantId, archives closed → new chain)
    → saveMessage
    → auto-match participant to CRM client
    → emit WebSocket events (conversation:new or conversation:updated + message:new)
```

### Queue & Assignment System

The queue system is the **single source of truth** for who receives conversations:

1. **Weekly Schedule** (`ClientChatQueueSchedule`): Managers define which operators work each day (Mon–Sun)
2. **Daily Override** (`ClientChatQueueOverride`): Managers can override today's queue without changing the weekly schedule
3. **No automatic assignment**: New conversations arrive as "unassigned"
4. **Join model**: Operators in today's queue see unassigned conversations and click "Join Conversation" to claim them
5. **Optimistic concurrency**: `joinConversation()` uses raw SQL `UPDATE ... WHERE assignedUserId IS NULL` to prevent race conditions

**Visibility rules:**
- Managers (superadmins) always see ALL conversations
- Operators in today's queue see their assigned conversations + unassigned conversations
- Operators NOT in queue see only their assigned conversations
- If no operators are scheduled, only managers see new conversations

### WebSocket Gateway (`clientchats.gateway.ts`)

**Namespace:** `/ws/clientchats`

**Rooms:**
| Room | Members |
|------|---------|
| `agents` | All authenticated agents |
| `agent:{userId}` | Specific agent |
| `managers` | Users with `client_chats.manage` permission |
| `queue` | Operators in today's queue |

**Events emitted (server → client):**
| Event | Payload | Target |
|-------|---------|--------|
| `conversation:new` | Conversation object | managers + (queue or agent:{assignedId}) |
| `conversation:updated` | Conversation object | managers + (queue or agent:{assignedId}) + previous agent |
| `message:new` | `{ conversationId, message }` | managers + (queue or agent:{assignedId}) |
| `operator:paused` | `{ conversationId }` | agent:{userId} |
| `operator:unpaused` | `{ conversationId }` | agent:{userId} |
| `reopen:requested` | `{ conversationId, userId }` | managers |
| `reopen:approved` | `{ conversationId }` | agent:{userId} |

No client → server events (no `@SubscribeMessage` handlers).

### Channel Adapters

Each adapter implements the `ChannelAdapter` interface:
- `verifyWebhook(req)` — Validate webhook signature
- `parseInbound(body)` — Parse raw webhook payload into `ParsedInboundMessage`
- `sendMessage(externalConversationId, text, metadata, media?)` — Send outbound message

| Adapter | Channel | Signature Method | Media Support |
|---------|---------|-----------------|---------------|
| WhatsApp | WHATSAPP | HMAC-SHA256 (`x-hub-signature-256`) | Text, image, video, audio, document, sticker, location, contacts |
| Telegram | TELEGRAM | Secret token header | Text, photo, document |
| Viber | VIBER | HMAC-SHA256 (`x-viber-content-signature`) | Text only |
| Facebook | FACEBOOK | HMAC-SHA256 (`x-hub-signature-256`) | Text only |
| WebChat | WEB | Always valid | Text only (no outbound push) |

### API Endpoints

**Public (no auth):** `public/clientchats/`
- `POST /start` — Start web chat session
- `POST /message` — Send web chat message (JWT token guard)
- `POST /webhook/{viber,facebook,telegram,whatsapp}` — Channel webhooks
- `GET /webhook/{facebook,whatsapp}` — Webhook verification

**Agent (JWT auth, `client_chats.menu`):** `v1/clientchats/`
- `GET /conversations` — List conversations (with filters)
- `GET /conversations/:id` — Get conversation detail
- `GET /conversations/:id/messages` — Get messages (paginated)
- `POST /conversations/:id/reply` — Send reply (text + optional file)
- `POST /conversations/:id/join` — Join unassigned conversation
- `PATCH /conversations/:id/assign` — Assign/unassign
- `PATCH /conversations/:id/status` — Change status
- `POST /conversations/:id/request-reopen` — Request reopen
- `GET /conversations/:id/history` — Previous conversation messages

**Manager (JWT auth, `client_chats.manage`):** `v1/clientchats/queue/`
- `GET /today` — Today's queue operators
- `GET/PUT /schedule` — Weekly schedule
- `PUT /override` — Set daily override
- `GET /live-status` — Live dashboard data
- `DELETE /conversations/:id` — Delete conversation
- `POST /conversations/:id/pause-operator` — Pause operator
- `POST /conversations/:id/approve-reopen` — Approve reopen

**Admin (JWT auth, `client_chats_config.access`):** `v1/clientchats/`
- `GET /channel-accounts` — Channel configuration
- `GET /analytics/overview` — Analytics overview
- `GET /analytics/by-agent` — Per-agent analytics

