### Page Composition (`page.tsx`)

The main page has two views toggled by managers:
1. **Inbox View**: `InboxSidebar` (left) + `ConversationPanel` or `EmptyState` (right)
2. **Manager Dashboard**: `ManagerDashboard` with tabs (Analytics, Active Operators, Live Dashboard, Queue & Schedule)

### Key Components

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `InboxSidebar` | Lists conversations with Live/Closed tabs, search, filters, unread badges, pagination. Listens to WebSocket events to update list in real-time. |
| `ConversationPanel` | Shows selected conversation: messages, reply box, "Join Conversation" button for unassigned chats, inactivity alerts, previous conversation history loading. |
| `ConversationHeader` | Displays customer name, channel badge, assigned operator. Actions: assign, close/reopen, pause/unpause, link client, delete. |
| `ReplyBox` | Text input with file attachment, canned responses (type `/`), WhatsApp templates. Managers bypass 24h window restriction. |
| `FilterBar` | Multi-select channel filter, assigned-to filter (managers only), search input. |
| `ManagerDashboard` | Tabbed dashboard: Chat Analytics (KPI cards, charts), Active Operators (online status), Live Dashboard (real-time metrics), Queue & Schedule. |
| `ManagerQueuePanel` | Today's queue management, weekly schedule editor, escalation config. |

### Display Name Resolution

The display name for a conversation follows this fallback chain:
```
CRM Client name → conversation.participant.displayName → "Unknown Customer"
```
Never falls back to raw channel IDs (e.g., `tg_5434592986`).

### WebSocket Hook (`useClientChatSocket`)

Connects to `/ws/clientchats` via Socket.IO. Returns `{ on, off, isConnected }`.

Used by:
- `InboxSidebar`: `conversation:new`, `conversation:updated`, `message:new`
- `ConversationPanel`: `message:new`, `conversation:updated`, `operator:paused/unpaused`
- `ManagerDashboard`: `escalation:warning`, `escalation:reassign`

### Notification Hook (`useNotifications`)

Manages browser notification permission and sound playback:
- Calls `unlockAudio()` before every `play()` as a safety net against autoplay policy
- On play failure, resets `audioUnlocked` flag for retry on next user interaction
- Keeps interaction listeners persistent (not removed after first click)

