## Database Schema

### Core Models

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `ClientChatChannelAccount` | Channel configuration (one per channel type) |
| `ClientChatConversation` | A conversation thread with a customer |
| `ClientChatParticipant` | A customer identity across channels |
| `ClientChatMessage` | Individual messages in a conversation |

### Queue & Assignment Models

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `ClientChatQueueSchedule` | Weekly operator schedule (day + userId) |
| `ClientChatQueueOverride` | Daily queue override (date + userIds array) |
| `ClientChatAssignmentConfig` | Legacy config (deprecated, kept for compatibility) |

### Supporting Models

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `ClientChatEscalationConfig` | SLA timeouts and escalation settings |
| `ClientChatEscalationEvent` | Escalation event log |
| `ClientChatCannedResponse` | Quick reply templates |
| `ClientChatWebhookFailure` | Webhook error log |

### Key Relationships

```
Conversation → ChannelAccount (which channel)
Conversation → Participant (the customer, via participantId)
Conversation → Client (linked CRM client, optional)
Conversation → AssignedUser (operator handling it, optional)
Conversation → PreviousConversation (conversation history chain)
Message → Participant (customer sender, null for agent messages)
Message → SenderUser (agent sender, null for customer messages)
Participant → MappedClient (auto-matched CRM client)
```

### Statuses

- `ClientChatStatus`: `LIVE` | `CLOSED`
- `ClientChatDirection`: `IN` (customer) | `OUT` (agent)
- `ClientChatAccountStatus`: `ACTIVE` | `INACTIVE`

